    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="287"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d287">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 657.119/451b</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        French Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_JJJ1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jusserand</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d287fn1">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                            mutandis</hi>, on the same date, to the British Ambassador on Special
                        Mission and to the Italian Ambassador.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 3, 1918</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: I hand you herewith a copy of
                    the rationing agreement entered into on April 30, 1918, by the War Trade Board
                    with <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_NF1">Fridtjof Nansen</persName>,
                    special representative of the Norwegian Government.</p>
                <p>I understand that previous to the execution of this agreement it was examined by
                    your representatives working in conjunction with the War Trade Board, and that
                    this agreement is entirely satisfactory to your Government.</p>
                <p>I should be glad if you would assure me that my understanding of this matter is
                    correct.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
